sponsoredPosts.text:
I make my videos super short because I feel like no one should listen to me for more than a minute.

Crazy insecurity! That‚Äôs why I‚Äôm doing the riskiest thing yet - I‚Äôm doing a 40 minute AUDIO show and I‚Äôm going all in. 100% honesty. 

It‚Äôs called Nas Talks - and the second episode just launched. It‚Äôs simple: just open Spotify and type Nas Talks. To my surprise, people are tuning in!

I hope you like the 40 min Nas more than the 1 minute Nas. Or else we have a problem ü§™

I hate making this video but it's necessary.

Whenever I promote a country, a product or a company, people assume and ask: ""how much did you get paid for this? credibility lost!"" 97% of the time the answer is $0. In fact, I PAID to do it. 
This is indicative of a much bigger problem where money comes in first and everything else comes second. The truth is, some stuff deserves to be amplified and shared and talked about to millions even if no money is involved. 
Take Singapore for example. I am really fascinated by this place in more than way. Some of the good stuff of Singapore comes from...the government. And by definition, I will promote the government even if there is no tourism board paying me. It's just the way it works. I care more about making a good video with a worthy message than anything else. 
Credibility is the most important thing in life. I never wanna lose it with you. And I hope this video provides a bit more transparency. 
In terms of money: 
Most of my money comes from two sources: 
1. Mid-roll ads on long videos (4-6 every month) 
2. Videos I make for companies on the side that go on THEIR channel
3. Nas Daily Agency
4. Speaking engagements / consulting. 
5. The occasional tourism board collaboration that is much more rare than you think. Twice in the Nas Daily history. 
Sponsorhips are a legitimate way for people to make money. And I do them some times. But I feel fortunate that money is no longer the most important element of Nas Daily, and I hope my videos communicate that message.

Thank you. Without your support, I am nothing.
